Description: Montou offers an online market place that enables its users to buy and sell used products.
Full Description: Montou fills a niche in the e-commerce market. Thrift. About 20% of the US population shops at thrift stores. Thrift is intrinsically green, is a great way of finding unique items, and it is inexpensive. (usually under $10) In the US, we throw away 47M tons of goods, that are not at the end of their usable life. ("durable goods")  This is money, being buried. Goodwill, the largest company in the thrift business makes 3B a year revenue from the 20k tons of durable goods donated to them. They are projected to grow 10% this year. The closest existing example of the Montou Network is Ebay. Montou will be different from Ebay in a lot of ways, but Ebay's numbers are the closest example. Ebay does 3.9B dollars worth of business a year. Of its 112.3M users, 1.3M are sellers. The 3.9B in revenue is generated by those 1.3M sellers.  These numbers place Montou at the convergence of two giant markets. Of the ways there are to sell online, NONE are centered on the thrift market. Other than stand-alone, e-commerce stores, thrift is missing from the online marketplace.  Why?  Fee scales. None of the existing platforms use a volume pricing scale, they all use a highest price per item model. This creates a barrier to entry for Thrift selling.  Montou wants to break down the barrier to having thrift online.

Your brand with one unified message. When people mention the term “brand,” they’re usually referring to a logo. But in reality, a brand is MUCH more than that. Yes, your logo is the cornerstone, but your messaging, your visual representation, your staff, your communication and your copy all work together to build your complete brand. Is your brand working for your business? Is it dated & irrelevant? Is it inconsistent or not fully developed? Does it match across all platforms from print to social media, digital to real life? The Outspective team provides the outside perspective you need to answer these questions and determine if you are right where you need to be, if it’s time for a refresh, or if your business needs to develop branding in the first place. Description: SILICON VALLEY INDICATORS are Find data about Silicon Valley’s economy and community health.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: The Silicon Valley Indicators website is a collection of charts, data, and resources relating to Silicon Valley’s economic and community health trends. A majority of the indicators presented here are published in Joint Venture’s annual publication, the Silicon Valley Index. Released every February at Joint Venture’s State of the Valley event, the Index is a nationally-recognized publication that has been telling the Silicon Valley story for nearly 20 years. The report not only publishes the data, but highlights challenges and provides an analytical foundation for regional decision-making. The Indicators website is a project of the Silicon Valley Institute for Regional Studies, housed within Joint Venture Silicon Valley, a non-profit public-private partnership based in San Jose, California. For additional information about the Institute or Joint Venture, visit www.jointventure.org.

Description: Galoo is a reverse buying platform that enables buyers to request prices for the preferred products and negotiate with sellers.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Galoo brings the art of negotiation to online trade and social shopping. It is a “patented” reverse buying platform that assists buyers in making intelligent pricing and sourcing decisions by letting them create their own buyer requests that are sent to thousands of sellers locally and worldwide for any product or service required. Unlike traditional auctions, daily deal or shopping sites, Buyers can search the Galoo site or create their own buyer requests by making an offer on the advertised price for listed Products or simply filling out a quick and easy online form, request a Service at the price they are willing to pay.  Buyers can also invite friends in order to strengthen their negotiating position through facebook, twitter and other social media sites or invite their favourite sellers to participate in the seller network themselves. Alternatively, buyers can also use the “Buy Now” button if the savings are already listed through Galoo's Price Comparison Partners.   The Galoo savings calculator also displays the buyer’s savings upon completion of the transaction and allow Buyers to contribute part of their savings to the charity of their choice through the Galoo save and donate system. All Sellers are invited to sign up to list the products and services they provide, as well as the geographic region taht they sell or offer their service in. Buy, sell, barter & save on everything you want & need! As a virtual worldwide shopping mall Galoo helps buyers save time, money and effort by bringing everything they want and need together in one place.  That includes tens of 1,000s of Buyers, Sellers, products and services to “Oooh!” and “Aaah!” over with every visit to the secure Galoo.com database. What’s more, Galoo's world is where everything is up for negotiation. The patented “reverse buying” concept puts a revolutionary twist on age old principles which have brought Buyers and Sellers together for centuries. In short, haggling and negotiation reign supreme in the Galoo marketplace.
